quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,152,"Verily, those who have taken to themselves a calf, there shall reach them wrath from their Lord, and abasement in the life of this world; for thus do we reward those who forge a lie"
  7,153,"But those who have done bad works, and then turn again after them and believe - verily, your Lord, thereafter, is Forgiving and Merciful"
  7,154,"And when Moses´ wrath calmed down he took up the Tables, in the inscription of which was guidance and mercy for those who fear their Lord"
  7,155,"And Moses chose from his people seventy men for Our appointment; and when the earthquake took them he prayed, \"O my Lord! Had you willed, you could have destroyed both them and me before this. Will Thou destroy us for what the fools amongst us have d"
  7,156,"And ordain for us good in this world, and in the Hereafter too; verily, we are guided unto Thee.\" He said, \"With My punishment, I fall on whom I will; but My mercy embraces everything; and I will ordain it for those who do right, and practice ch"
  7,157,"Those who follow the Messenger - the unlettered Prophet - whom they find mentioned in their own Law and Gospel. (Deuteronomy18 and Johnbidding them what is just (reasonable) and forbidding them what is wrong (evil, unreasonable, stupid); and making lawful"